      <h1 class='title'>Trooper David Clarke</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 16 September 2004 vol 424 cc1768-9WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_1768ws' title='Col. 1768WS &mdash; HC Deb 16 September 2004 vol 424 c1768WS' name='column_1768ws' href='#column_1768ws' rel='bookmark'>1768WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_660'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-david-kidney' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_660' title='Link to this speech by Mr David Kidney' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-david-kidney" title="Mr David Kidney">Mr. Kidney</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">To ask the Secretary of State for Defence what progress he has made in the investigation of the
          <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_1769ws' title='Col. 1769WS &mdash; HC Deb 16 September 2004 vol 424 c1769WS' name='column_1769ws' href='#column_1769ws' rel='bookmark'>1769WS</a>
          death of Trooper David Clarke; what communications he has had with the family of Trooper David Clarke about the progress of the investigation; and if he will make the results of the investigation public. [188585]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_661'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-ivor-caplin' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_661' title='Link to this speech by Mr Ivor Caplin' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-ivor-caplin" title="Mr Ivor Caplin">Mr. Caplin</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">The Royal Military Police Special Investigation Branch (SIB) have completed an investigation into the incident in whim Trooper (Tpr) Clarke and his colleague Corporal Allbutt died. An Army Board of Inquiry (BOI) is ongoing.</p><p>It is not departmental policy to release publicly copies of either SIB or BOI reports. However, regular contact is being maintained with Tpr Clarke's family, who are informed of all significant developments on the various processes under way. The family will receive a copy of the final BOI report when this becomes available.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
